    <sec id="Sec8">
      <title>Consistent orientation of long reads</title>
      <p id="Par42">For perfect data it is possible to consistently determine the reading direction of each read relative to the genome from which it derives. This is not necessarily the case in real-life data. The relative orientation of two reads is implicitly determined by the relative orientation of overlapping reads, i.e., by the signature <inline-formula id="IEq170"><alternatives><tex-math id="M339">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
