				\begin{document}$$e_i \prec e_k$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M878"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi>i</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>≺</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi>k</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2021_186_Article_IEq487.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. This scenario cannot appear on neighboring edges, as the shared node has a unique order of <italic>s</italic> and <inline-formula id="IEq488"><alternatives><tex-math id="M879">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
