				\begin{document}$$s \prec s'' \prec s'$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M914"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mo>≺</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>′</mml:mo><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:msup><mml:mo>≺</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>s</mml:mi><mml:mo>′</mml:mo></mml:msup></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="13015_2021_186_Article_IEq505.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. The resulting graph <italic>M</italic> is cycle free and thus uniquely defines the positions of all unitigs. Nodes represent the sequence of the common interval on the unitig <italic>s</italic> as attributed to the clique <inline-formula id="IEq506"><alternatives><tex-math id="M915">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
